# Normalize line endings to LF in the repo and on checkout.
#
# Why: the working tree is edited from both a Windows host and a Linux
# devcontainer against the same files, which produces the intermittent
# CRLF/LF churn noted in HANDOFF.md. Forcing LF everywhere (eol=lf) stores
# LF in the repo AND checks out LF on every platform, so neither side sees
# the other's edits as spurious line-ending changes. GitHub Pages serves
# LF files without issue.
#
# NOTE: after committing this file, run `git add --renormalize .` once (best
# done at the start of a session, not the end) to rewrite any already-tracked
# files that were stored with CRLF. That produces a one-time line-ending-only
# diff; commit it on its own so it doesn't muddy a content change.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files: never touch their bytes.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.svg  text eol=lf
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.xlsx binary
*.xls  binary
